            ></path></svg
          >
          <h4 class="text-xl font-medium text-white">Hybrid Rendering</h4>
          <p>
            Astro's ability to combine dynamic rendering on the landing page
            with static generation for recipe pages provided the perfect balance
            of flexibility and performance for this use case.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <br />
      <p>
        The recipe filtering and search system is built with React for
        interactivity:
      </p>
      <CodeBlock
        code={`// Add recipe filtering code here`}
        language="typescript"
      />
      <p>
        Future enhancements include adding a recipe submission form that
        generates pull requests with new Markdown files, implementing a
        measurement converter for switching between imperial and metric units,
        adding print-friendly styling optimized for recipe cards, and creating a
        meal planning feature to help organize weekly menus.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</CaseStudyLayout>

<style>
  a {
    color: var(--header-color);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--header-color);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    font-weight: 600;
    display: inline-block;
    position: relative;
  }

  @media (hover: hover) {
    a {
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:after {
      bottom: 0;
      content: "";
      height: 2px;
      left: 50%;
      position: absolute;
      background: var(--header-color);
      transition:
        width 0.2s ease 0s,
        left 0.2s ease 0s;
      width: 0;
    }
    a:hover:after {
      width: 100%;
      left: 0;
    }
  }

  code {
    background-color: #1e1e1e;
    color: #d4d4d4;
    font-family: "Martian Mono", "Courier New", Courier, monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    padding: 0.125rem 0.375rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid #333;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    code {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
    }
  }

  :global(.case-study-layout) .card-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  :global(.case-study-layout) .card {
    background-color: var(--card-color);
    border: 1px solid #333;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    width: calc(33.33% - 0.67rem);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  :global(.case-study-layout) .card h4 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    :global(.case-study-layout) .card {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
